<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99857063450671></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99857063450671><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=99857063450671>RE: Need help raising my Necro...I'm a newbie.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=99857063450671#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=79214><span id=Scholar>Ravensveil</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>243 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 23rd 8:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.06]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Question 1: do you have your pet spell? For pet casters, this is probably your most important spell. <br>2: are you using life-tap religiously?<br><br>I found Nek to be difficult because of how far the mobs are from guards. But, it can be done. <br><br>Get that pet. Cast him and arm him. If you have to, go buy a rusty weapon first. You'll need bones, but you can usually by them. Some characters will sell them, or even in some cases give them to you. Next, hotkey your basic pet commands. Your most important ones: /pet attack /pet guard me /pet guard here<br><br>Remember that life tap spell? IMHO, that line of spells is what really defines us as one of the most powerful classes. Each time you are casting that spell, you are casting a sort of minor healing on yourself. You'll notice it better at lvl 4. But casting that spell religiously will save your life.<br><br>Basic strategy: target mob and con. Make sure you want to attack it. Cast life tap. hotkey pet to attack. cast sap str. cast life until mob is dead. step in to melee if mob is refusing to die.<br><br>If something agro's you, immediately hit your pet attack key (as the attacking mob will be in your target now) as soon as you do that, run away. Pause if you think it is a mob you can handle, finish off whatever your pet was fighting and then assist your pet. If it is more than you can handle, then keep running for the guards. You can always recast your pet.<br><br>My other tip is to group. Really, all you need is a partner, either a pure tank or another pet caster. Either will suit you. I do well with an enchanter. Clerics are good because of the heals. Warriors are good because they can take the brunt of the attack while you play good caster and let your pet assist the tank. If your tank is doing well, then don't send in your pet. Have him guard you back. That way, when the Grizzly comes up, he will agro your pet, and you can tell your tank that it is time to run for the guard.<br><br>I hope I told you something useful. If you have trouble finding a partner and you're still having trouble in Nek, the trek to west freeport. The newbie zone is safer. If you go through the wall a the left side (left if you are in the fighting yard facing the gate) there is a DE who will buy/sell. You take no bad faction hits for the orcs here, and you aren't KoS right now. The guards will also assist you. It is a little bit easier and will carry you until you can hunt neriak without immediately dying when a grizzly attacks. just don't head into freeport. There are places where you will be kos.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
